# Cubit Patterns

## State types

- `Cubit<DefaultState<T>>` — single-result operations (fetch, submit, delete)
- `Cubit<PaginationState<T>>` — paginated list screens
- Never use `Bloc` with events unless the feature has genuinely complex event-driven logic.

## Emit order: `loading` → `success` / `fail`

```dart
class GetUserCubit extends Cubit<DefaultState<UserModel>> {
  final UserRepository _repo;

  GetUserCubit({required UserRepository repo})
      : _repo = repo,
        super(const DefaultState.init());

  Future<void> getUser(String id) async {
    emit(const DefaultState.loading());
    final result = await _repo.getUser(id);
    result.fold(
      (failure) => emit(DefaultState.fail(failure)),
      (user)    => emit(DefaultState.success(user)),
    );
  }
}
```

## BlocProvider — always provide from `injector` at the page level

```dart
class UserPage extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return BlocProvider(
      create: (_) => injector<UserCubit>(),
      child: const _UserView(),
    );
  }
}
```

The private `_UserView` (`StatefulWidget`) handles the form state and calls the cubit.

## AppDialog — always in `BlocListener`, never in `BlocBuilder`

```dart
BlocListener<UserCubit, DefaultState<UserModel>>(
  listener: (context, state) {
    state.when(
      init:    () {},
      loading: AppDialog.showLoading,
      success: (_) {
        AppDialog.dismiss();
        context.goNamed(AppRoutes.home);
      },
      fail: (failure) {
        AppDialog.dismiss();
        AppDialog.showError(message: failure.message);
      },
    );
  },
  child: ...,
)
```

Available dialogs: `showLoading()` · `dismiss()` · `showSuccess(title, message)` · `showError(message)` · `showConfirm(title, onConfirm)`.
